version_description: Chords and lyrics for "Come, Worship the King" by Michael W. Smith and Shane and Shane. "Glory Revealed" album version: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3htDU3don7U.
This specific tab is based off the studio recorded version (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VRGFv7bakFI).

The A and A2 instead of the G and C used in the other versions is closer to the original, It's also in a much better key for high tenors like myself. Dlourishes can be added with a trill on the D's and a strong accent can be places on the E's.
Corrected timing formatting and chords, completed verses.

version_description: The only other chords tab for this song only showed the chord progression of each line, not where each chord should go in relation to the words. This tab was formatted to be simpler and easier to read.
To get the correct timing on this song takes practice. Lot's of subtle syncopation. Play this with a Capo on the first fret to use these easier chords. I think the original key is on the 3rd fret.
